## 06_transitivity (TIMEOUT)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 06 - Transitive relation (multi-hop)
% 'r' is transitive with r(a,b), r(b,c), r(c,d); therefore r(a,d).
% Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(r_decl, type, r: $i > $i > $o ).
thf(a_decl, type, a: $i ).
thf(b_decl, type, b: $i ).
thf(c_decl, type, c: $i ).
thf(d_decl, type, d: $i ).

thf(r_transitive, axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i, Z: $i] :
      ( ( ( r @ X @ Y ) & ( r @ Y @ Z ) ) => ( r @ X @ Z ) ) ).
thf(r_ab, axiom, r @ a @ b ).
thf(r_bc, axiom, r @ b @ c ).
thf(r_cd, axiom, r @ c @ d ).

thf(goal, conjecture, r @ a @ d ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

