## 08_drinker (THM)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 08 - Drinker paradox (Smullyan)
% In any non-empty domain there is someone such that, if they drink,
% then everyone drinks:   |-  ?x. ( drinks(x) => !y. drinks(y) )
% Needs classical logic (excluded middle); no axioms. ($i is non-empty.)
% Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(drinks_decl, type, drinks: $i > $o ).

thf(goal, conjecture,
    ? [X: $i] : ( ( drinks @ X ) => ( ! [Y: $i] : ( drinks @ Y ) ) ) ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

