## 09_barber (THM)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 09 - Barber paradox (Russell)
% No one shaves exactly those people who do not shave themselves:
%   |-  ~ ?b. !x. ( shaves(b,x) <=> ~ shaves(x,x) )
% No axioms; the contradiction comes from instantiating x := b.
% Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(shaves_decl, type, shaves: $i > $i > $o ).

thf(goal, conjecture,
    ~ ( ? [B: $i]
        : ! [X: $i]
          : ( ( shaves @ B @ X ) <=> ( ~ ( shaves @ X @ X ) ) ) ) ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

