## 10_group_right_inverse (TIMEOUT)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 10 - Group theory: a left inverse is also a right inverse
% From associativity, a left identity e, and left inverses inv,
% prove   !x. mult(x, inv(x)) = e.
% A classic non-trivial equational theorem (genuine search for a prover).
% Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(mult_decl, type, mult: $i > $i > $i ).
thf(inv_decl,  type, inv:  $i > $i ).
thf(e_decl,    type, e:    $i ).

thf(associativity, axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i, Z: $i]
    : ( ( mult @ ( mult @ X @ Y ) @ Z ) = ( mult @ X @ ( mult @ Y @ Z ) ) ) ).
thf(left_identity, axiom, ! [X: $i] : ( ( mult @ e @ X ) = X ) ).
thf(left_inverse,  axiom, ! [X: $i] : ( ( mult @ ( inv @ X ) @ X ) = e ) ).

thf(goal, conjecture, ! [X: $i] : ( ( mult @ X @ ( inv @ X ) ) = e ) ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

