## 15_equivalence_classes (TIMEOUT)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 15 - Equivalence classes are well-defined
% For an equivalence relation r,  r(x,y)  implies that x and y are
% related to exactly the same elements.   Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(r_decl, type, r: $i > $i > $o ).

thf(reflexive,  axiom, ! [X: $i] : ( r @ X @ X ) ).
thf(symmetric,  axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i] : ( ( r @ X @ Y ) => ( r @ Y @ X ) ) ).
thf(transitive, axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i, Z: $i] :
      ( ( ( r @ X @ Y ) & ( r @ Y @ Z ) ) => ( r @ X @ Z ) ) ).

thf(goal, conjecture,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i] :
      ( ( r @ X @ Y )
     => ( ! [Z: $i] : ( ( r @ X @ Z ) <=> ( r @ Y @ Z ) ) ) ) ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

