## 19_combinatory_skk (TIMEOUT)

```elixir
{res, stats} = prove ~p"""
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
% 19 - Combinatory logic: S K K behaves as the identity combinator
% With the reduction rules for K and S, prove  !x. ((S K K) x) = x.
% (apply is left-associative application.)   Status : Theorem
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
thf(apply_decl, type, apply: $i > $i > $i ).
thf(k_decl,     type, k: $i ).
thf(s_decl,     type, s: $i ).

thf(k_rule, axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i] : ( ( apply @ ( apply @ k @ X ) @ Y ) = X ) ).
thf(s_rule, axiom,
    ! [X: $i, Y: $i, Z: $i]
    : ( ( apply @ ( apply @ ( apply @ s @ X ) @ Y ) @ Z )
      = ( apply @ ( apply @ X @ Z ) @ ( apply @ Y @ Z ) ) ) ).

thf(goal, conjecture,
    ! [X: $i]
    : ( ( apply @ ( apply @ ( apply @ s @ k ) @ k ) @ X ) = X ) ).
%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
""", stats: true

format_result res
```

